default young people with Special 
defaultEducational Needs (SEN)
default.
default In addition to this, the government has also issued Inclusive Schooling guidance that sets out practical advice for schools and local authorities on inclusive practices.
default The guidance promotes 7 key prin
defaultciples of an inclusive education service:
defaultIt goes further to state that inclusive schools have:
defaultThe SEN system is currently being reformed as part
default of the Children and Families Bill that is passing through Parliament. As part of these reforms, (due to be implemented as of September 2014) the current Code of Practice and the Inclusive Schooling guidance is being merged into a single 0-25 SEN Code of P
defaultractice.
defaultThe draft version of this document is still not finalised, but it has several sections on inclusion, principally set out on pages 86-88. For example it sets out that "where a child or young person has SEN but does not have an EHC plan they must b
defaulte educated in a mainstream setting barring very certain circumstances".
defaultThe new Code of Practice also refers to the provisions of the Equality Act, which include school and local authority duties not to discriminate against, and must make reasonable adjust
defaultments for, disabled children. Public bodies are also under wider duties to promote equality of opportunity.
defaultInclusive employment practicedefaultPeople with a learning disability are more excluded from the workplace than any other group of disabled people. Research shows 65% of people with a learning disability want to work, and that with the right support they make highly valued employees. However
default, only 7% of adults with a learning disability are in paid employment, and even then it is often for part-time hours and low pay. 
defaultMencap believes that:
defaultThere are many barriers to people with a learning disability accessing employment, including employer prejudice. However, Mencap believes that people with a learning disability should also get the support they need to get and keep real 
defaultpaid jobs in mainstream settings and that, in order to help achieve this, the government should increase supported employment provision for people with a learning disability and guarantee long-term funding for this support. The definition of supported empl
defaultoyment is as follows:
defaultThis model is based on a number of important principles:
defaultIn order to foster a truly inclusive society, Mencap believes that people with a learning disability should be proper
defaultly and meaningfully included in the workplace and be given the opportunity to get and hold down a job. Employers should make reasonable adjustments where required and, in addition to these obligations, Access to Work funding is available to pay for aids an
defaultd adaptations, transport costs, a communicator at a job interview, a support worker job coaches. 
defaultPractice guidance around inclusivedefaultMencap has produced its 'I Want To Work' guide for employers that highlights good p
defaultractice in employing people with a 
defaultlearning disability
default.
